# React Component Rules

- Always use functional components — never class components
- Props interface defined directly above the component, named `[Name]Props`
- Default export at the bottom of the file
- Hooks called only at the top level of components or custom hooks
- Extract any logic > 5 lines into a custom hook in frontend/src/hooks/
- Use React.memo() on widgets that receive stable props to prevent re-renders
- Loading states: show a skeleton UI — never just blank space or a spinner alone
- Error states: show an inline error message with a retry button
- Empty states: show a descriptive empty state with an icon
- Never put API calls directly in components — use custom hooks
- Event handler functions named with `handle` prefix: handleClick, handleSubmit, etc.
